reviews.text: Station closed. Im allready missed my train and late to work. Peoples standing outside and waiting. Unbelievable.

I was horrendously stoped by a man wearing the southern rail uniform asking me to stop taking a picture. He had no manners whatsoever not to say it is utterly unfair and bonkers. I like to take pictures of urban unusual buildings and a facade of one of those facing the rail caught my attention. For the first time in my whole time living in London this uncomfortable  unfortunate event happen.

What a joke there is nobody operating tills there are both windows closed and you have two workers behind the gate women dressed like is her day off and a guy in uniform both are on the phone minding there on business what a joke and they get paid too. What a absolute disgrace
Unhelpful staff not remotely interested in doing what they are being paid for
